<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1065,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1065,1090]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">Description.</emphasis>
Dorsal, lateral, and ventral views are shown in 
<figureCitation box="[863,978,1065,1090]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,312,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[170,1417,301,1527]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 16. Ghatsa montana, CAS-SU 39871 (holotype), 46.4 mm SL. (A) Dorsal, lateral, and ventral views, Puthutotam Estate, brook in Anamallai Hills, India; (B) radiograph. Photos by CAS, Ichthyology Section." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288026/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Figure 
<number box="[947,978,1065,1090]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
. Measurements and meristic counts are given for the only specimen available to us, the 
<typeStatus box="[688,786,1101,1126]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[800,901,1102,1126]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fxd1-0prj" name="California Academy of Sciences, Stanford University Collection" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">CAS-SU</collectionCode>
<number box="[909,984,1102,1126]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="39871.0">39871</number>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[1052,1150,1101,1126]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[1183,1283,1101,1126]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.64" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="46.4">46.4 mm</quantity>
SL, 
<quantity box="[1336,1436,1101,1126]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4799999999999995" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="54.8">54.8 mm</quantity>
TL. Body (depth: 
<number box="[362,411,1138,1162]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="10.1">10.1</number>
% SL, width: 
<number box="[576,626,1137,1162]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="13.5">13.5</number>
% SL) arched predorsally, tapers posterior of anal-fin origin to caudal base, flattened ventrally. Head (length: 
<number box="[603,654,1174,1198]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="21.7">21.7</number>
% SL, width: 
<number box="[815,866,1173,1198]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="76.2">76.2</number>
% HL, depth: 
<number box="[1029,1080,1173,1198]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="44.5">44.5</number>
% HL) triangular when viewed dorsally; tubercles absent. Snout length 
<number box="[654,705,1209,1234]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="47.5">47.5</number>
% HL. Orbit (length: 
<number box="[990,1041,1210,1234]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="22.8">22.8</number>
% HL) small, ovoid, positioned dorsolaterally, shorter than interorbital width (
<number box="[667,718,1246,1270]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="31.7">31.7</number>
% HL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1065,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Mouth (
<figureCitation box="[301,368,1281,1306]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,267,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[150,1436,267,1335]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oral morphology of (A) Homaloptera cf. ocellata, UF 161718, 64.1 mm SL; (B) Homalopteroides wassinkii, UMMZ 155660, 46.2 mm SL; (C) Homalopterula ripleyi, ANSP 188908, 43.1 mm SL; (D) Balitoropsis zollingeri, UF 166094, 52.1 mm SL; (E) Pseudohomaloptera tatereganii, RMNH 7632 (holotype), 64.6 mm SL; (F) Ghatsa montana, (holotype) CAS- SU 39871, 46.4 mm SL. Abbreviations: CF, central furrow; FL, fleshy lobe; FP, fleshy pad; LJ, lower jaw; LL, lower lip; LRB, lateral-rostral barbel; MB, maxillary barbel; MRB, medial-rostral barbel; RC, rostral cap; UJ, upper jaw; UL, upper lip." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288015/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number box="[355,368,1281,1306]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
F) (width: 
<number box="[494,545,1281,1306]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="25.7">25.7</number>
% HL) subterminal, large portions of upper and lower jaws visible. Lips thin, smooth, crescentic, continuous around corners of mouth; widest at corners of mouth. Lower lip medially interrupted; the chin extending to most anterior portion of lip. Rostral and postlabial grooves present. Two pairs of rostral barbels, 
<number box="[332,346,1390,1414]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of maxillary barbels. Medial-rostral barbels widely separated from one another, distance equal to that of medial interruption of lower lip. Medial and lateral-rostral barbels unequal in size, separated by distance about equal to length of lateral-rostral barbel. Lateral-rostral barbel not reaching base of the barbel, maxillary barbel reaching horizontally to vertical at anterior nostril. Gill opening extends to ventral surface of body. Dorsal fin (base length: 
<number box="[505,541,1534,1558]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="9.7">9.7</number>
% SL, length: 
<number box="[711,761,1533,1558]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="18.5">18.5</number>
% SL) originates posterior to pelvic-fin base and closer to caudal-fin base than to snout (predorsal length: 
<number box="[693,744,1569,1594]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="54.3">54.3</number>
% SL). Pectoral fin (length: 
<number box="[1065,1116,1569,1594]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="26.8">26.8</number>
% SL) longer than head, not reaching pelvic-fin origin. Pelvic fin (length: 
<number box="[666,717,1606,1630]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="20.8">20.8</number>
% SL) lacks axillary pelvic lobe, not reaching anus; anus closer to anal-fin origin than to pelvic-fin insertion. Anal fin length 
<number box="[842,892,1641,1666]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="13.5">13.5</number>
% SL. Adipose keel on caudal peduncle. Caudal peduncle length 
<number box="[336,386,1677,1702]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="15.9">15.9</number>
% SL, depth 9.0% SL. Caudal fin truncate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1065,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Body scaled except for ventral surface anterior to pelvic-fin insertion. Scales small, smooth, not obvious to naked eye (
<figureCitation box="[278,346,1749,1774]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1660,1682]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,193,1638]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[155,1432,193,1638]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Scale sizes and keel patterns of predorsal region: Large, and keeled scales, (A) Balitoropsis zollingeri, UF 166094, 52.1 mm SL; (B) Pseudohomaloptera tatereganii, RMNH 7632 (holotype), 64.6 mm SL. Large, and wart-like / keeled scales (C) Homalopteroides wassinkii, UF 183330, 43.6 mm SL. Medium, and keeled scales, (D) Homaloptera cf. ocellata, UF 161718, 64.1 mm SL. Small, and smooth scales, (E) Homalopterula ripleyi, ANSP 188908, 43.1 mm SL; (F) Ghatsa montana, CAS-SU 39871 (holotype), 46.6 mm SL. Scale bar represents 1 mm. Left side of photo is anterior." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288014/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number box="[331,346,1750,1774]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Total lateral-line pores ca. 
<number box="[681,725,1750,1774]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="101.0">101</number>
, predorsal scales ca. 
<number box="[960,990,1749,1774]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="53.0">53</number>
, circumpeduncular scales ca. 
<number box="[1323,1354,1749,1774]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="60.0">60</number>
. Scales above and below lateral line ca. 
<number box="[525,553,1786,1810]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="18.0">18</number>
and ca. 
<number box="[653,683,1785,1810]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="15.0">15</number>
, respectively. Scales below lateral line to pelvic-fin origin ca. 
<number box="[1401,1432,1786,1810]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="12.0">12</number>
. Dorsal-fin rays iii, 
<number box="[364,379,1821,1846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
½; anal-fin rays ii, 
<number box="[590,606,1821,1846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="5.0">5</number>
; pectoral-fin rays vi, 
<number box="[845,859,1822,1846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="9.0">9</number>
for left side, and a total of 
<number box="[1162,1190,1821,1846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="15.0">15</number>
rays for the right side (right fin damaged; simple and branched rays could not be differentiated); pelvic-fin rays ii, 
<number box="[1182,1196,1858,1882]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="8.0">8</number>
for left side and iii, 
<number box="[1422,1436,1858,1881]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
for right side; total caudal-fin ray count 
<number box="[608,639,1893,1918]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="16.0">16</number>
. Pores of cephalic lateralis system: 
<number box="[1045,1059,1894,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
supraorbital, 
<number box="[1216,1230,1893,1918]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[1246,1272,1893,1918]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="11.0">11</number>
infraorbital, 
<number box="[1422,1436,1894,1917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="7.0">7</number>
preoperculomandibular, and 
<number box="[472,486,1930,1954]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="3.0">3</number>
supratemporal. Total vertebrae count 
<number box="[912,940,1930,1954]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="38.0">38</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[955,1038,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1549,1571]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,312,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[170,1417,301,1527]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 16. Ghatsa montana, CAS-SU 39871 (holotype), 46.4 mm SL. (A) Dorsal, lateral, and ventral views, Puthutotam Estate, brook in Anamallai Hills, India; (B) radiograph. Photos by CAS, Ichthyology Section." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288026/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
Fig. 
<number box="[1008,1038,1929,1954]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1065,2026]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1965,1990]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81">Coloration</emphasis>
. In 
<number box="[374,404,1966,1990]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="70.0">70</number>
% ethanol: The specimen is faded, and the general color of the body is brown with a black stripe along the lateral-line. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herre" box="[471,667,2001,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" refString="Herre, A. W. C. T. (1945) Notes on fishes in the Zoological Museum of Stanford University: XX, New fishes from China and India, a new genus, and a new Indian record. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 35, 399 - 404." type="journal article" year="1945">
Herre (
<number box="[551,609,2001,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="1945.0">1945</number>
: 
<number box="[613,659,2001,2026]" pageId="24" pageNumber="81" value="400.0">400</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
gave the following description: “The color in alcohol is brown, the underside yellowish; 
<number box="[391,419,152,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="10.0">10</number>
short dark brown bars across the back, but not extending down to the lateral-line; a poorly defined dark longitudinal stripe below the lateral line from the eye to the caudal base; top of head very dark brown; a blackish-brown spot on the ventral base; caudal with a blackish blotch on its base and another near its tip; other fins all clear.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">Distribution</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[413,461,296,320]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
locality is the Puthutotam Estate, brook in Anamallai Hills, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1260,1320,295,320]" name="India" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">India</collectingCountry>
, elevation about 
<quantity box="[221,334,332,357]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.09728" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" unit="ft" value="3600.0">3,600 feet</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[350,435,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="25.[151,250,2003,2025]" captionTargetBox="[235,1344,493,1967]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[228,1360,481,1981]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 17. Type localities for species of Ghatsa. Asterisk represents the type species of the genus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288027/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[404,435,332,356]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). This is in the state of Tami Nadu close to the border with Kerala, Coimbatore District; estimated coordinates are 
<geoCoordinate box="[455,564,367,392]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" precision="555" value="10.36">
<number box="[455,520,367,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="10.36">10.36</number>
° N
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[579,684,367,392]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" precision="555" value="76.93">
<number box="[579,645,367,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="76.93">76.93</number>
° E
</geoCoordinate>
. This drainage was reported to be adjacent and northeast to the Chalakudy basin by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pethiyagoda" box="[380,778,404,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" refString="Pethiyagoda, R. &amp; Kottelat, M. (1994) Three new species of fishes of the genera Osteochilichthys (Cyprinidae), Travancoria (Balitoridae) and Horabagrus (Bagridae) from the Chalakudy River, Kerala, India. Journal of South Asian Natural History, 1, 97 - 116." type="journal article" year="1994">
Pethiyagoda &amp; Kottelat (
<number box="[660,721,404,428]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="1994.0">1994</number>
: 
<number box="[725,770,404,428]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" value="110.0">110</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1173,2003,2025]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288027/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="82" targetBox="[235,1344,493,1967]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1173,2003,2025]" box="[151,1173,2003,2025]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,2003,2025]" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">FIGURE 17.</emphasis>
Type localities for species of 
<taxonomicName box="[590,663,2003,2025]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Ghatsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[590,663,2003,2025]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="82">Ghatsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Asterisk represents the type species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation author="Menon" box="[199,360,152,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Menon, A. G. K. (1987) The fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Pisces. Vol. IV. Teleostei - Cobitoidea. Part 1. Homalopteridae. Zoological Survey of India, i - x, 1 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1987">
Menon (
<number box="[294,352,152,176]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[468,600,153,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[468,600,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Silent Valley and New Amarambalam of the Western Ghats, but this is likely 
<taxonomicName box="[248,350,188,212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pillaii">
<emphasis box="[248,350,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. pillaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Remarks). 
<bibRefCitation box="[534,832,188,213]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Arunachalam, M., Johnson, J. A. &amp; Rema, Devi, K. (2002) Homaloptera santhamparaiensis, a new species of balitorid fish (Teleostei: Balitoridae) from a Western Ghats stream of Kerala, India. Acta Zoologica Taiwanica, 13, 31 - 37." type="journal article">
Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[692,742,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[765,824,188,212]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined an individual from Kerala at Malakkapara, headwaters of Chalakudy River. This specimen (
<collectionCode box="[697,762,224,248]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vj5p-iy27" name="Kerala Forest Research Institute" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">KFRI</collectionCode>
F. 
<number box="[797,840,224,248]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="107.0">107</number>
) was not examined in this study, and this locality for 
<taxonomicName box="[151,283,261,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[151,283,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,295,320]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Menon" box="[325,489,296,320]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Menon, A. G. K. (1987) The fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Pisces. Vol. IV. Teleostei - Cobitoidea. Part 1. Homalopteridae. Zoological Survey of India, i - x, 1 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1987">
Menon (
<number box="[423,481,296,320]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName box="[632,737,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pillaii">
<emphasis box="[632,737,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. pillaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(spelled 
<emphasis box="[845,904,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">pillai</emphasis>
) as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1339,297,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[1204,1339,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Menon" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Menon, A. G. K. (1987) The fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Pisces. Vol. IV. Teleostei - Cobitoidea. Part 1. Homalopteridae. Zoological Survey of India, i - x, 1 - 259." type="book chapter" year="1987">
Menon (
<number box="[159,217,332,356]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined only the 
<typeStatus box="[453,501,333,357]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName box="[614,717,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pillaii">
<emphasis box="[614,717,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">H. pillaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but gave different counts than those in the original description (also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pethiyagoda" box="[259,599,367,392]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Pethiyagoda, R. &amp; Kottelat, M. (1994) Three new species of fishes of the genera Osteochilichthys (Cyprinidae), Travancoria (Balitoridae) and Horabagrus (Bagridae) from the Chalakudy River, Kerala, India. Journal of South Asian Natural History, 1, 97 - 116." type="journal article" year="1994">
Pethiyagoda &amp; Kottelat 
<number box="[537,599,368,392]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[602,647,368,392]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="109.0">109</number>
). Many authors (Indra &amp; Rema Devi 
<number box="[1080,1139,368,392]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1981.0">1981</number>
; Madhusoodana Kurup &amp; Radhakrishnan 
<number box="[330,389,404,428]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="2010.0">2010</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arunachalam" box="[404,695,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Arunachalam, M., Johnson, J. A. &amp; Rema, Devi, K. (2002) Homaloptera santhamparaiensis, a new species of balitorid fish (Teleostei: Balitoridae) from a Western Ghats stream of Kerala, India. Acta Zoologica Taiwanica, 13, 31 - 37." type="journal article" year="2002">
Arunachalam 
<emphasis box="[565,618,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[636,695,404,428]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Silas" box="[711,833,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Silas, E. G. (1953) Classification, zoogeography and evolution of the fishes of the cyprinoid families Homalopteridae and Gastromyzonidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 50, 173 - 263." type="journal article" year="1953">
Silas 
<number box="[776,833,404,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1953.0">1953</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) have given a pectoral-fin ray count of iv, 
<number box="[1344,1358,404,428]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="8.0">8</number>
for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="83">G. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The pectoral-fin ray count here and in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Herre" box="[968,1098,439,464]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" refString="Herre, A. W. C. T. (1945) Notes on fishes in the Zoological Museum of Stanford University: XX, New fishes from China and India, a new genus, and a new Indian record. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 35, 399 - 404." type="journal article" year="1945">
Herre 
<number box="[1041,1098,439,464]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="1945.0">1945</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) is vi, 
<number box="[1175,1191,440,464]" pageId="26" pageNumber="83" value="8.0">8</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
